Steps to Install PostgreSQL 14.7 on Windows 10 and Set Up Northwind Database
----------------------------------------------
Install PostgreSQL
Configure Environment Variables
Verify the Installation
Download the Northwind PostgreSQL SQL file
Create a New PostgreSQL Database
Import the Northwind SQL file
Verify the Northwind database installation
Connect to the Database Using Jupyter Notebook
Prerequisites

Step 1: Install PostgreSQL
Download PostgreSQL 14.7 for Windows 10 from:
PostgreSQL 14.7 Installer
Save the installer executable and run it.
During installation, create the default postgres user and set a password.
Note: Version 14.7 is recommended because it’s widely used and stable.

Step 2: Configure Environment Variables
Add PostgreSQL’s bin folder to the Windows PATH so commands can be run from anywhere.
Right-click Windows icon → System.
Click Advanced system settings.
In the System Properties dialog, click Environment Variables.
Under System Variables, select Path → click Edit.
Add: C:\Program Files\PostgreSQL\14\bin.

Step 3: Verify the Installation
Open Command Prompt (Win + R → cmd).
Run: psql --version → should return installed version.
Connect to PostgreSQL:
psql -U postgres
Enter the password set during installation.
If successful, you’ll see the postgres=# prompt.

Step 4: Prepare Northwind Database Directory
Create a directory:
mkdir northwind && cd northwind
Download the SQL file:
curl -O https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pthom/northwind_psql/master/northwind.sql
(Or manually save the file into the directory).

Step 5: Create the Northwind Database
Log in to PostgreSQL as the postgres user:
psql -U postgres
Create a new database:
CREATE DATABASE northwind;
Exit psql:
\q

Step 6: Import the Northwind SQL File
Make sure you’re in the northwind directory where northwind.sql is saved.
Run the import:
psql -U postgres -d northwind -f northwind.sql
This loads all tables and data into the new database.

Step 7: Verify Northwind Database Installation
Connect to the Northwind database:
psql -U postgres -d northwind
List all tables:
\dt
(Should show tables like categories, customers, employees, orders.)
Run a sample query:
SELECT * FROM customers LIMIT 5;
Exit psql:
\q

Step 8: Connect PostgreSQL to Jupyter Notebook (Optional but Recommended)
Install SQL extension:
!pip install ipython-sql
Load the SQL extension inside Jupyter:
%load_ext sql
Connect to Northwind database:
%sql postgresql://postgres@localhost:5432/northwind
If a password is required:
%sql postgresql://postgres:{password}@localhost:5432/northwind
(Replace {password} with the one you set during installation)
Example with variable connection string:
connection_string = f'postgresql://postgres:{"4Projects"}@localhost:5432/northwind'
%sql $connection_string
